<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Lemon juice:</strong>&nbsp;It may have citric acidic, but it’s far too acidic and can cause dark spots to appear after sun exposure. It can also dry and irritate your skin.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Baking soda:</strong> At a pH level of 8, baking soda will stress your skin, significantly decreaseTrusted Source your skin’s water content, and cause dry skin.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Garlic:</strong>&nbsp;In raw form, garlic can cause skin allergies, eczema, skin inflammation, and watery blisters.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Toothpaste:</strong> The ingredients in toothpaste may kill germs and absorb oil, but they can also dry out or irritate your skin.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Sugar:</strong>&nbsp;As an exfoliant, sugar is too harsh for the skin on your face.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Vitamin E:</strong>&nbsp;Topical application of vitamin E can irritate your skin and is not proven to improve scar appearance.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
